%% Sequence Diagram: CronJob -> kagent A2A -> Tool Execution
%% Each arrow has a comment noting the smoke test that verifies it

sequenceDiagram
    participant CJ as CronJob Pod
    participant KA as kagent Controller
    participant AP as Agent Pod (AutoGen)
    participant LL as LiteLLM
    participant OL as Ollama (192.168.5.2)
    participant MM as MetaMCP
    participant AG as agentgateway
    participant MCP as MCP Server
    participant MEM as Memory CRD (k8s)

    Note over CJ,MEM: Scheduled Agent Task Execution

    %% Step 1: CronJob triggers agent task
    %% Smoke: kubectl create job --from=cronjob/test-agent test-run
    CJ->>+KA: POST /a2a/tasks/send<br/>{"task": "daily-report", "agent": "reporter"}

    %% Step 2: kagent creates agent pod
    %% Smoke: kubectl get pods -l kagent.dev/agent=reporter --watch
    KA->>KA: Lookup Agent CRD "reporter"<br/>Resolve ModelConfig, Tools
    KA->>+AP: Create agent pod<br/>Mount Tool configs, ModelConfig

    %% Step 3: Agent loads previous memory
    %% Smoke: kubectl get memory reporter-memory -o jsonpath='{.status.entries}'
    AP->>MEM: GET Memory CRD "reporter-memory"
    MEM-->>AP: Previous context + state

    %% Step 4: Agent calls LLM for planning
    %% Smoke: kubectl exec deploy/kagent -- wget -qO- http://litellm:4000/health
    AP->>+LL: POST /v1/chat/completions<br/>model: qwen2.5:14b<br/>tools: [filtered tool list]
    LL->>+OL: POST /v1/chat/completions<br/>api_key: ollama
    OL-->>-LL: completion with tool_calls[]
    LL-->>-AP: tool_calls: [{name: "query_postgres", args: {...}}]

    %% Step 5: Agent routes tool call through MetaMCP -> agentgateway
    %% Smoke: kubectl exec deploy/metamcp -- wget -qO- http://agentgateway:8080/health
    AP->>+MM: MCP tools/call "query_postgres"<br/>workspace: "reporter"
    Note over MM: Verify tool "query_postgres"<br/>is in reporter's namespace
    MM->>+AG: MCP tools/call "query_postgres"<br/>JWT auth

    %% Step 6: agentgateway routes to MCP server
    %% Smoke: curl http://agentgateway.genai.127.0.0.1.nip.io/mcp/tools/list
    AG->>+MCP: Execute tool via stdio/SSE<br/>Per-server credentials
    MCP-->>-AG: Tool result (JSON)
    AG-->>-MM: Tool result
    MM-->>-AP: Tool result

    %% Step 7: Agent calls LLM with tool results
    %% Smoke: same as step 4
    AP->>+LL: POST /v1/chat/completions<br/>messages: [..., tool_result]
    LL->>+OL: POST /v1/chat/completions
    OL-->>-LL: Final completion (report text)
    LL-->>-AP: Report text

    %% Step 8: Agent stores result in Memory CRD
    %% Smoke: kubectl get memory reporter-memory -o yaml | grep -A5 'entries'
    AP->>MEM: PATCH Memory CRD<br/>Append task result + timestamp

    %% Step 9: Agent pod reports completion and terminates
    %% Smoke: kubectl get pods -l kagent.dev/agent=reporter --field-selector=status.phase=Succeeded
    AP-->>-KA: Task complete<br/>status: succeeded
    KA-->>-CJ: A2A task response<br/>{"status": "completed"}

    Note over CJ,MEM: Agent pod terminates. Memory persists in CRD.
